  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically includes:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Most countries have specific legislation criminalizing money laundering\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Specialized financial crime units\n\n6. Key Compliance Mechanisms\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Regular audits\n- Staff training programs\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between jurisdictions\n- Extradition treaties\n- Mutual legal assistance agreements\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
